<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/946:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-10">December 10, 1941</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                    December 10—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>530. Last evening Uruguayan Senate voted to send brief telegram
                                informing United States Senate that invoking principles of
                                international justice and humanity Uruguayan Senate condemns
                                aggression of which United States has been the object.</p>
                            <p>Herrerista Senators were in majority and message as approved was that
                                proposed by them after more strongly worded Colorado text had been
                                defeated.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>